#originalTopic=Debate:_Armed_pilots_in_airplanes
It's better to arm pilots and risk abuse than risk another 9/11. Dave Kopel &amp; David Petteys. "Air Neglect". National Review Online. July 2, 2003 - "the airline executives would rather risk another 9/11 than take the (tiny) chance that an armed pilot might use his gun illegally, and the airline might be sued." 
